## Constants layout — RBAC vs other constants

Three layers — **never merge**:

| Layer | Path | Holds |
|-------|------|--------|
| **RBAC permission codes** | `web-admin/lib/constants/permissions/{domain}-perm.ts` | `HELP_PERMISSIONS`, `MARKETING_PERMISSIONS`, … |
| **Other domain constants** | `web-admin/lib/constants/{domain}.ts` | statuses, enums, flags — **not** RBAC codes |
| Contract **types** | `web-admin/lib/auth/access-contracts.ts` | `PageAccessContract` |
| Route **contracts** | `web-admin/src/features/*/access/*-access.ts` | `routePattern`, `page`, `actions`, `apiDependencies` |

### ✅ Use `lib/constants/permissions/{domain}-perm.ts` (new RBAC codes)

Keeps permission codes separate from `inventory.ts`, `payment.ts`, etc.

```ts
// lib/constants/permissions/help.ts
export const HELP_PERMISSIONS = {
  PLATFORM_INVENTORIES: 'help:platform_inventories',
} as const
export type HelpPermissionCode = (typeof HELP_PERMISSIONS)[keyof typeof HELP_PERMISSIONS]
```

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **File** | `lib/constants/permissions/{domain}-perm.ts` |
| **Export** | `export const {DOMAIN}_PERMISSIONS = { … } as const` |
| **Import in** | `*-access.ts`, `page.tsx`, `app/api/**/route.ts` |
| **Legacy** | flat `lib/constants/help.ts` may re-export — prefer `permissions/` for new code |

### ❌ Do NOT use `src/features/*/access/*-permissions.ts` for codes

| Reason | Detail |
|--------|--------|
| RBAC codes are **global** | `orders:read` is not owned by one feature folder |
| Import direction | `app/api/` and `lib/` should not depend on `@features/…` for permission strings |
| Split brain | Contract in `marketing-access.ts`, codes in `marketing-permissions.ts` — still need `*-access.ts` for routes; adds a third file with no ingest benefit |
| Cross-feature use | `core-access.ts` would import from `features/help/access/` — wrong boundary |

**`*-access.ts` stays the only contract file** under `src/features/*/access/`.

### ❌ Do NOT use

| Path | Why |
|------|-----|
| `lib/constants/access-contracts/` | Route contracts belong in `*-access.ts` |
| RBAC codes in `lib/constants/inventory.ts` | Stock/inventory enums — different domain |
| Permission only in constants, no `*-access.ts` | Missing from inventories + inspector |

### Import chain (no gaps)

```
DB sys_auth_permissions_cd
  → lib/constants/permissions/{domain}-perm.ts   ({DOMAIN}_PERMISSIONS)
  → *-access.ts                              (import + use in page / actions / apiDependencies)
  → page.tsx + app/api/.../route.ts          (same import)
```

Legacy: permission blocks inside `settlement-catalog.ts` etc. — **do not bulk-move**; new codes go in `permissions/`.

