## Complete vs incomplete

| Scenario | Complete when |
|----------|----------------|
| **New permission + new route** | Steps 0–6 all done |
| **Existing permission, new route** | Steps 1–4 + 6 (no new migration if code exists) |
| **Contract-only change** | Edit `*-access.ts` → check → sync |
| **Open route (no perm)** | `page: {}` + `notes` in contract; no fake `RequireAnyPermission` |
| **Auth-only API** | `apiDependencies` with `notes` explaining auth-only; no `requirePermission` mismatch in docs |
| **UI in `features/foo/ui/`** | Contract still in route-mapped `*-access.ts`; gate on `page.tsx` |

---

## WRONG (always a gap)

| Anti-pattern | Gap |
|--------------|-----|
| Permission only in `lib/constants/` | No inventory / no route mapping |
| Gate only in `features/**/ui/*.tsx` not imported by `page.tsx` | Wire audit + convention miss |
| `fetch('/api/…')` not in `apiDependencies` | Inventory / docs drift |
| Hardcoded `'foo:read'` in page, different string in contract | Silent mismatch |
| RBAC codes in wrong domain file (e.g. `inventory.ts`) | Confusion with non-RBAC constants |
| `src/features/*/access/*-permissions.ts` for RBAC codes | APIs/`lib` must not import permission strings from `@features/` |
| `lib/constants/access-contracts/` for route contracts | Wrong layer; not ingested |
| New `*-access.ts` not in registry | Inspector omits contracts |
| Sidebar link without nav dual-write | Menu vs RBAC drift |
| New permission only in TS / contract, no migration | RBAC checks fail |

---

## Legacy note

Many `*-access.ts` files use inline permission literals (e.g. `'promotions:read'`). **Do not refactor bulk.** For **new** routes: prefer `lib/constants` imports. Strings must still match DB exactly.

